					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Vellum codex; third of the three uniform volumes; Sefardi square script of 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex</support>
								<extent>186 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>300</height>
										<width>240</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>185</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>186 folios (+ 4 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 1 older and 4 modern unfoliated paper flyleaves at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>24 quires: i-xvi8 (folios 1-128), xvii6 (folios 129-134), xviii-xxii8 (folios 135-142, 143-150, 151-158, 159-166, 167-174), xxiii-xxiv6 (folios 175-186). </p>
									<p>Catchwords. On guards.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="26" writtenLines="26">
									<p>Hair side and flesh side distinguishable. Ruling with hard-point visible.</p>
									<p>Masorah magna in two lines in the upper margin and three lines in the lower margin.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script, punctuated. <name type="person" role="patron">Shemu᾿el ben Shemu᾿el ibn Musa</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, <name type="place">Lisbon</name>, <date calendar="Hebrew">5243</date>  [<date calendar="Gregorian">1483</date>]: folio 185v. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Yosef ben Yudah Elhakhim</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon (185v). </p>
							<p>Scribal note in a micrographic design with a date <date calendar="Hebrew">Kislev 5200</date> [<date calendar="Gregorian">1440</date>], which should be <date calendar="Hebrew">5243</date>  (50r).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house. Green leather, gold-tooled Star of David on the inner and outer cover.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Hebrew Bible. Lisbon 1484-53. Hagiographa. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2628.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
